<subSubSection id="C32E65595CA3FF0648A6F8EDFE73FEBD" lastPageId="189" lastPageNumber="190" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B36D25CA3FF0748A6F8EDFA52F827" blockId="188.[151,1437,1230,2011]" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CA3FF0748A6F8EDFEF5F8B6" bold="true" box="[199,315,1842,1867]" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CA3FF074AD5F8ECFCAAF8B6" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[692,868,1843,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufosignatus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CA3FF074AD5F8ECFCAAF8B6" box="[692,868,1843,1867]" italics="true" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">A. rufosignatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the antennal flagellomeres short; the clypeus with the median clypeal carina higher than frons level; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the eye small; the frons strongly 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CA3FF074922F8A5FE70F86E" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[323,446,1914,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriaceous">coriaceous</taxonomicName>
; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle forming a right angle; the ocelli small; the metapostnotal-propodeal suture straight; the mesopleuron with the lower fovea not divided and the mesopleural suture opened; the paramere shorter than the basiparamere; and the cuspis with the arms very short, whereas 
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CA3FF074DE5F81CFA52F827" box="[1412,1436,1987,2010]" italics="true" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">A.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B36D25CA2FF0648F6FF47FE73FEBD" blockId="189.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="189" pageNumber="190">
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CA2FF0648F6FF47FEEDFF4D" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[151,291,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="189" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufosignatus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05CA2FF0648F6FF47FEEDFF4D" box="[151,291,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="189" pageNumber="190">rufosignatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the antennal flagellomeres long; the clypeus with the median clypeal carina lower than frons level; the antennal scrobe carinate; the eye large; the frons 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515CA2FF064A84FF63FCAEFF28" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[741,864,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="189" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriaceous">coriaceous</taxonomicName>
; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle obtuse; the ocelli very small; the metapostnotal-propodeal suture convergent to the first metapostnotal carina; the mesopleuron with the lower fovea divided and the mesopleural suture closed; the paramere longer than the basiparamere; and the cuspis with the arms long.
</paragraph>
